The paper proposes a multi-objective evolutionary algorithm driven by generative adversarial networks (GANs) for optimization problems. This work involves machine learning models and optimization algorithms, which are closely related to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
